  "response": "There is no single \"first Hindu\" in history. Hinduism is one of the world's oldest religions, with roots and evolution that span thousands of years. It developed gradually over time, emerging from the ancient Vedic culture in the Indian subcontinent around 1500-1200 BCE. The religious practices and beliefs evolved from the traditions of the Indus Valley Civilization and the Aryan peoples who migrated to the region. Rather than having a founder like some other religions, Hinduism emerged as a complex, diverse religious and cultural tradition that developed organically over centuries.",
